1. Get the virgin app (45 days) before cruising and book as much as you can. 
2. Book the earliest time to board if you can, a lot of entertainment you need to book once on the ship. If you‚Äôre late you miss out. 
3. Book the unlimited spa first day (more than just treatments, full haven of rest & rejuvenation).
4. Don‚Äôt peak on the first night (took a full day in the sauna to recover)
5. Room service is free (I found out on the last day).
6. Seasoned cruisers can be savage (especially at the buffet). 
7. Wifi is not free (just get the premium package)
8. Payment is all in USD.
9. Bring seasickness tablets and take them before you get sick. 
10. Plan your days as much as you can before you board!
